hydro-morphologically dynamic area as major river the Ganges, The Brahmaputra 
and The Meghna join together and find their way to the Bay of Bengal 
through this region. Amtali Upazilla in Barguna district located in the south 
central hydrological region of Bangladesh is categorized as exposed coastal 
upazila comprises of only one agro-ecological region named the Ganges Tidal 
Floodplain. The land type of this area is mainly medium high land where the maximum 
flooding depth is about 90 cm during the monsoon season. Sea 
level rise impacts become reality in this area as historical observation shows 
that almost on the coastline the rate of water level rise is found to be 0.53 
cm/year during 1977-2002 also projected to rise by 35 cm end of this century. Though the water and 
sanitation coverage of Bangladesh has significantly increased but the issue of 
WASH resiliency and sustainability still remains as big concern as consequence of climate change impacts. In this area safe 
water sources and its infrastructure along with sanitation facilities are 
becoming threating due to gradually increasing salinity, tidal influence, 
unusual rainfall, and cyclone and storm surge. Through this project WaterAid 
Climate Resilience Programme will try to promote resiliency for WASH 
services with addressing rights for climate vulnerable people. Project will play 
a key role in local water and sanitation planning and implementation taking 
consideration of climate change impacts and adaptive capacity to cope with 
changing global phenomena. This requires huge capacity building support to 
community, piloting of appropriate technology and approach with effective 
engagement of local government and relevant stakeholders. Aligning with programmatic 
objectives, this project intended to achieve five specific changes: increase 
access to safe water and improved sanitation for poor and excluded in climate 
vulnerable area, proper hygiene practice among household members and school 
children improved, increase awareness on climate resilience and water safety 
compliance, improve resilience and inclusive WASH facilities at institutions 
and public places, improve leadership role of local government institutes in 
planning, coordinating and monitoring WASH services.</font></p> <h2><font style="font-size: 12pt;" color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif"></font><font style="font-size: 12pt;" face="Arial,sans-serif">2. What?</font></h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><strong><font style="font-size: 12pt;" color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif">Project theme</font></strong><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;– This project will promote 
