yle="width: 28.76%; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; border-width: medium 1pt 1pt medium; border-style: none solid solid none; border-right: 1pt solid rgb(127, 127, 127); border-bottom: 1pt solid rgb(127, 127, 127); text-align: left;"> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-size: 16px;">Head of Programmes</span></p> </td> <td width="18%" valign="top" style="width: 18.8%; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; border-width: medium 1pt 1pt medium; border-style: none solid solid none; border-right: 1pt solid rgb(127, 127, 127); border-bottom: 1pt solid rgb(127, 127, 127); text-align: left;"> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">DD/MM/YYYY</font></p> </td> </tr> </tbody></table> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"></font><em><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">The project statement is a very short&nbsp;outline of a project (maximum two pages) that a team is proposing to implement, subject to funding.&nbsp;</font></em></p> <h2><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"></font><font face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">1. Why?</font></h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"></font><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Bangladesh has made 
tremendous progress in dealing with open defecation (OD) and has recently 
achieved almost zero open defecation rate. However, to sustain the progress, 
the country need to invest more and find out ways to help people climb 
sanitation ladder. Currently, 62% of the population are using improved toilets. 
Bringing the remaining 38% to improve sanitation coverage is a challenge since 
they mostly fall under lowest economic strata of the society. Similarly, 13% 
people in the country is using unimproved source of drinking water. This 
population also needs support to move out from unimproved to improved sources 
of water.  
 
&nbsp; 
 
Although microfinance 
has played a tremendous role in alleviating widespread rural poverty in the 
country, the applicability of microfinance to develop water and/or sanitation 
has not been tested yet. Since investing in water and sanitation does not 
provide any tangible benefit, and cash income to help poor people repay the 
loan, it might also be difficult for the poor people to adopt this strategy. For 
the same reason, water and sanitation has not been considered as a ‘product’ by 
the MFIs considering the associated repayment risk.  
 
&nbsp; 
 
However, considering 
the long-term potential benefits of introducing microfinance for WASH 
development, WaterAid has tested a model whereby, demand for improved WASH has 
been created by the WASH facilitators in the community, and then link them with 
MFIs to access credit. However, considering WASH as a new product, and to 
minimize the repayment risk, the social mobilization part has to be more 
intensive compared to CLTS or other approaches. Emerging evidence suggest that 
the approach works well and can be scaled up.&nbsp;</span></p> <h2><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"></font><font face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">2. What?</font></h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"></font><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Objective 
and Outcomes:</span> 
</strong> 
&nbsp; 
 
</span></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">The 
project will create demand for improved WASH services and promote microfinance 
services to help communities improve their household WASH facilities. The 
project will help MFIs to develop customised product and ingrain fairly easy 
terms of lending and repayment to attract potential clients who wish to improve 
their WASH facilities.  
 
&nbsp; 
</span></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; text-decoration: underline;"> 
<strong>Programmatic 
Approach: 
</strong> 
&nbsp; 
</span></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> 
The project will intervene to arrange the provision 
of conditional loans for the poor households/ families for upgrading, reconstruction 
and maintenance of their WASH facilities (Water points/sources and toilets) to 
convert them into improved ones. Special loan product will be developed and given 
to poor households for establishing WASH facilities. The project will also work 
with the local level entrepreneurs to use different promotional mechanism to 
accelerate uptake of different WASH products. &nbsp;This will be done to encourage the institution to 
operate this service and promote WASH as a product for microfinance. Alongside, awareness raising sessions to promote the use of hygienic 
and improves toilets will take place to raise and ensure the demand for the 
facility. &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"> 
 
<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Expected 
outcome:</strong></span></font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">the project will allow roughly 9,000 households to have 
access to safe water and improved sanitation. This will help them for timely 
repairs while also generating funds for major repairs or additional 
construction. The project is thus expected to contribute in the sustainability 
of the WASH interventions already implemented; while stimulating demand and 
supply for improved WASH solutions to many others who cannot afford it 
otherwise. Moreover, WASH in not yet considered as a product for micro finance. 
This project will be a pilot initiative for the MFIs to understand that WASH 
could be a product for investment through micro credit. By addressing the financial constraints the project will contribute to 
SDG-6 and help communities pass through the sanitation ladder.&nbsp;</font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">Estimated timeframe: 36 months</font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">Estimated cost: GBP 300,000&nbsp;</font></p>  <h2><font face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">3. Where?</font></h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"></font>&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 12pt;">This project will be implemented in Durgapur Upazila of Rajshahi District. Poor households with unhygienic sanitation condition will be targeted in this project.</span></p> <h2><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"></font><font face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">4. Who?</font></h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"></font><span style="font-size: 16px;">Yet to be decided.</span></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-size: 16px;">&nbsp;</span></p> <table width="100%" style="width: 100%;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"> <tbody><tr> <td width="24%" valign="top" style="background: rgb(242, 242, 242) none repeat scroll 0% 0%; width: 24.72%; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; border: 1pt solid rgb(127, 127, 127); text-align: left;"> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><strong><font face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">Name of programme</font></strong></p> </td> <td width="75%" valign="top" style="width: 75.28%; padding: 0cm 5.4pt; border-width: 1pt 1pt 1pt medium; border-style: solid solid solid none; border-top: 1pt solid rgb(127, 127, 127); border-right: 1pt solid rgb(127, 127, 127); border-bottom: 1pt solid rgb(127, 127, 127); text-align: left;" colspan="3"> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;">&nbsp;</p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td width="24