Dhaka, Bangladesh.</span></p> <h2><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"></font><font face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">2. What?</font></h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"></font>&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 12pt;">Objective</span></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"> 
 
  
  
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
  
  
  
 
  
  
The overall objective of this project is to improve health and social 
wellbeing of the poor and disadvantaged tea-pickers by providing them with the 
access to safe drinking water, improved sanitation and at the same time influencing 
their health and hygiene practices. 
 
Teagarden workers, being one of the marginalized 
communities are deprived of these basic facilities. The project will thus mainly 
focus on improving water supply and sanitation facilities in the communities 
where they live. More specifically the project is aimed at doing the following: 
 
 
·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">Small-scale piped water network will be built and 
deep tube well will be constructed. This will ensure that they do not have to 
walk long distance to collect safe drinking water or use contaminated surface 
water. Existing 
unimproved and non-functional water points will also be renovated for use. 
 
&nbsp; 
 
·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
</font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">Communities and 
schools will be supported with improved sanitation facilities. Facilities 
provided in institutions will be disable-friendly and will have Menstrual 
Hygiene Management facilities in separate female chambers.  
 
&nbsp; 
 
·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
</font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">To ensure that the 
people understand and practice improved hygiene behaviour, such as hand-washing 
with soap at critical times and safe disposal of waste, awareness raising 
session and campaigns will be held. Social mobilisation will be carried out to 
influence their hygiene behaviour especially hand-washing practice with soap 
and menstrual health and hygiene management of adolescent girls and women of 
reproductive-age. 
 
&nbsp; 
 
·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
</font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">To further motivate 
and habituate to practice hand washing, the project will disburse hand washing 
devices in the communities. </font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"> 
 
The intervention will take place with the support from local government 
and tea-garden authorities and influence to strengthen the existing trends of 
coordination and engagement of local government, tea estate authorities for a 
sustainable WASH provision and management. 
</font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"> 
Expected outcomes 
</font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">The project will transform lives of 3,000 teagarden 
workers and their family members including children with access to safe 
drinking water. More than 2,000 workers including their family members are 
expected to stop open defecation or use of unhygienic fixed-place defecation, 
following construction of improved sanitation facilities (toilets). The project 
will also rigorously motivate 2,500 community people irrespective of age and 
gender to adopt hand washing practices with soap at critical times. Hygiene 
motivation will also reach adolescent girls about improving their menstrual 
health and hygiene management. Apart from 
providing access to safe drinking water and improved sanitation facilities, the 
inclusion will bring an impact on family wellbeing and rights of the deprived 
teagarden workers in terms of protecting their human and social dignity, 
reducing incidence of water borne diseases, improved hygiene behaviour and 
sanitation practices. 
 
</font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">Sustainability 
</font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"> 
Responsibility for operation and maintenance of the water options will 
be sold to the teagarden authorities through discussion and appreciations. They 
will allocate necessary resources for this purpose. A group of workers from 
among the beneficiaries will be trained on operation and maintenance of the 
facilities. They will take care of small repairing jobs. For major repairing, 
the community groups will be connected with local technicians and vendors who 
will attend the major maintenance work on call. Local government (Union 
Council) will be influenced to keep budgetary provision in their annual budget 
to provide sanitation subsidy (materials sus as ring, slab, sato pan etc) in 
the subsequent years. The workers will also demand contribution from the garden 
authorities to feed hardware maintenance activities that would be required in 
the subsequent years.</font></p>  <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><strong><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">Estimated cost</font></strong><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;–452,000 GBP</font></p> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><strong><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">Estimated timeframe</font></strong><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;–40 Months</font></p>  <h2><font face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">3. Where?</font></h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">This project will be implemented in selected tea gardens of Sreemangal upazila of Moulovibazar district.</span></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">The 
