result areas directly in its holistic approach. While the cross-sector (WASH &amp; health) priorities of the project aim to improve WASH and primary health 
services, as well as the integration of the two; and provide wider 
environmental health solutions through resilient technologies that are 
sustainable in the long run; the implementation means will focus on initiating 
or revitalising democratic processes towards the attainment of the human right 
to water and sanitation. Finally, it is expected that access to safe water and 
sanitation, improved hygiene behaviour, and more effective healthcare services 
will reduce the disease burden and cut down on losses of productive time, 
thereby increase the economic and human potential of people living in slums.</span></font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font style="font-size: 12pt;" color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px;">The desired 
change is to have ‘health and resilient Urban Poor communities with access to 
inclusive, resilient WASH and WASH integrated health services’ in the in the 
three cities and three municipalities where the project interventions will be 
carried out. The three key conditions to make this change happen are: 
 
 
 WASH 
     deprivation and public health risks in the target communities are addressed 
 WASH 
     integrated public health services ensured for the urban poor 
 Policy 
     and practice on WASH and health changed to reflect better integration 
 
 
&nbsp; 
 
To address these 
above mentioned conditions, target 
communities will be mobilised and empowered to get access to and maintain 
climate resilient WASH services, local authorities will be mobilised and 
sensitised to plan and implement community based environmental safety 
initiatives for public health benefit, primary healthcare clinics and service 
centres in proximity with target communities will be better equipped with WASH 
facilities and practices, front line healthcare workers will be capacitated, and 
gaps and opportunities for integration of resilient WASH in national and local 
level policy and programmes will be identified through policy analysis, 
scientific research and documentation of best practices.</span></font></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><font style="font-size: 12pt;" color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px;"> 
 
