Madagascar is far from achieving universal 
access to WASH. Madagascar did not reach its MDG 2015 targets and based on the 
current trends, it will also not attain the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) 
in 2030 unless significant changes are made. 
 
&nbsp; 
 
Almost half of the population of Madagascar 
does not have access to water. There are significant disparities between access 
to water in urban (82%) and rural (35%) areas. Women and girls are also 
disproportionately affected by a lack of access to clean water and basic 
sanitation. Except for some areas in southern Madagascar, there are, in fact, 
abundant natural water resources which are relatively accessible but remain 
untapped. However, these same water resources are threatened by the expected 
effects of climate change.  
 
