nt>&nbsp;</p> <h2><font style="font-size: 12pt;" color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif"></font><font style="font-size: 12pt;" face="Arial,sans-serif">1. Why?</font></h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt;"> 
Madagascar 
reports some of the worst water and sanitation statistics in the world and is 
slipping away from the 2030 goal of universal access to WASH[1]. 
The challenges to accelerate and expand the use of improved, sustainably 
managed WASH services are three-fold: Weak WASH governance, monitoring, and 
management capacities; Weak private sector/WASH supply; and Unhealthy 
behaviors/low demand for WASH.&nbsp; Through 
RANO WASH, we will increase equitable and sustainable access to WASH services 
to maximize the impact on human health and nutrition and preserve the 
environment in 250 rural communes in Vatovavy Fitovinany, Antsinanana, Amoron’i 
Mania, Haute Matsiatra, Vakinakaratra, and Alotro Mangoro.  
 
</p><p style="margin-bottom: 0pt;"> 
 
Our project 
posits the following development hypothesis:  
 
1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
if WASH governance and systems, 
and capacities to manage WASH services accountably are strengthened; 
 
2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
if quality WASH products and 
services are reliably available and affordable for all;  
 
3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
and if demand for improved WASH 
behaviors and services grows in an expanded consumer market;  
</p> <h2><font style="font-size: 12pt;" color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif"></font><font style="font-size: 12pt;" face="Arial,sans-serif">2. What?</font></h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt;"><font style="font-size: 12pt;" color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif"></font> 
 
Project theme – Increasing and improving private sector 
engagement in WASH service delivery. 
 
</p><p style="margin-bottom: 0pt;"> 
 
Mains Activities 
: (a)Design and implement a comprehensive 
WASH market assessment (WMA), to be conducted in four parts to allow greater 
depth and analysis in each area: 1) water supply construction and private 
sector managers (WSP); 2) sanitation markets and artisans; 3) WASH products and 
commercial enterprises; and 4) loan products and MFI or VSLA groups. 
 
(b)&nbsp; Develop a common methodology for 
conducting six regional private sector development plans for WASH services and 
products 
 
(c)&nbsp; Improve the Design, Construction 
&amp; Management of WASH Infrastructure 
 
</p><p style="margin-bottom: 0pt;"> 
 
Estimated cost – This project is fully 
unfunded. The estimated cost is 1,379,322 $ 
(for WaterAid intervention area - Alaotra Mangoro region) 
</p><p style="margin-bottom: 0pt;"> 
 
The total duration of the project 
is 5 years. This means 60 month of which there will be an annual planning of 
activities of 12 months each year 
</p><p style="margin-bottom: 0pt;"> 
 
Existing WaterAid experience – WaterAid has developed and implemented a rural water and sanitation 
project for the 6 intervention regions since 2000 through the development of 
WASH services in collaboration with the implementing partner. Support must be 
provided to the municipality for the setting up of the Municipal WASH Technical 
Service (STEAH), and efforts must then be made to improve their skills and 
abilities to build collaboration within the local WASH sector. WaterAid also 
supported the setting up of the WASH CSO network for the intervention areas, as 
well as the Regional Diorano-WASH Committee. These structures will provide 
technical support to the municipal structures that will be set up. 
Additionally, the strategic orientation of Diorano-WASH and that of the 
national WASH CSO and their experiences in other localities will be used in the 
project to ensure that these municipal structures are efficient. 
 
</p><p style="margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p> <h2><font style="font-size: 12pt;" face="Arial,sans-serif">3. Where?</font></h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt;">The project will be implemented in 250 
rural communes in Vatovavy Fitovinany, Antsinanana, Amoron’i Mania, Haute 
Matsiatra, Vakinakaratra, and Alotro Mangoro. 
 
The project will target 55,000 
people through a range of paid service options (public water connections, and 
social and private metered connections) 
</p> <h2><font style="font-size: 12pt;" color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif"></font><font style="font-size: 12pt;" face="Arial,sans-serif">4. Who?</font></h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt;"><font style="font-size: 12pt;" color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif"></font>&nbsp; 
 
This project will be implemented by WaterAid, 
in partnership with Catholic Relief Services (CRS), CARE, and local partners 
Bushproof and Sandandrano, 
 
