 </p> <h2><font color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;"></font><font face="Arial,sans-serif" style="font-size: 12pt;">2. What?</font></h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong><span color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif">Project theme</span></strong><span color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif">&nbsp;– What are the main WASH areas that this project focuses on and the main activities that will be implemented?</span></span></p> <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong><span color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif">Estimated cost:&nbsp;</span></strong><span color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif">GBP 600,000</span></span></p> <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong><span color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif">Estimated time frame: </span></strong><span color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif">36 months</span></span></p> <p style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong><span color="black" face="Arial,sans-serif">Existing WaterAid experience:&nbsp;</span></strong>WaterAid piloted the human rights based approach to 
citizen empowerment from 2011 to March 2016 that sought to put human rights at 
the center of development and citizens, especially the poor and marginalized as 
active agents of their own development. The work was implemented in six 
districts of Rumphi, Karonga, Machinga, Chikhwawa, Kasungu and Balaka. Following 
the formation of citizen forums and committees, training orientation&nbsp; on HRBA which also targeted the VDCs and 
ADCs, and implementation of community action plans, citizens successfully 
lobbied for provision of a borehole and a healthy facility in Kapyanga in 
Kasungu district. 
 
In Balaka, the citizen forums and committees 
successfully lobbied for the provisions of water to 53,000 community members 
through the Mpira Balaka Rural Water Supply Scheme.&nbsp; Through the project, WA learnt that 
empowering citizens can change power relationships between citizens and duty 
bearers and contribute towards improving responsiveness of duty bearers and generate 
drive among citizens to improve their sanitation and hygiene status.  
 
WA’s long term plan is to build the capacity of 
