  on functionality of sanitation infrastructure in public places such as 
  schools, markets and health care facilities, it has been observed that 
  maintenance of public sanitation infrastructure is also a challenge. After 
  considerable investments and years of use, sanitation infrastructure is often 
  abandoned due to poor maintenance. In addition to lack of adequate 
  community/institution based systems for operation and maintenance, local 
  councils usually have no funds to support even essential maintenance needs of 
  the infrastructure. In most cases, WASH technologies in use cannot be sustained 
  by communities due to financial and technical problems. The lack of adequate 
  skilled staff at district level has had a significant impact on the ability 
  to provide the required technical support to sustain water facilities in 
  communities and institutions.  
  &nbsp; 
