  Irrigation and Water Development is alarming, currently at 67%, and the Ministry does not have 
  a clear strategy to capacitate the District Councils.  
  &nbsp; 
  In 
  addition, the country is increasingly becoming water stressed due to human 
  activities, environmental degradation and climate. This has negatively 
  impacted on water resources, both in terms of quality and quantity. The 
  action by policy makers is usually insufficient to deal with the growing 
  water security challenges. There are conflicting policies, for example, between the Ministries responsible 
  for Irrigation and Environment, respectively, on land use practices and 
  catchment protection. Where policies or regulations exists there is poor 
  enforcement of catchment protection measures. On top of conflicting policies, 
  there is inadequate investments in catchment protection and water 
  conservation structures. </span></p><p style="margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt;">The project will be implemented under the Sector Engagement and Influencing (SEI) programme and will contribute to&nbsp;outcome 2 of the program, which is "I</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt;">mproved Action on 
